-- Taiwan Stocks: Power Mate Technology, Rexchip Electronics, Via
-- B y   E e   C h i e n   C h u a
-- 2012-06-04T05:54:12Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-04/taiwan-stocks-power-mate-technology-rexchip-electronics-via.html
Shares of the following companies had
 unusual  moves in  Taiwan trading . Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the close in Taipei. The
benchmark Taiex Index fell 3 percent to 6,894.66, the biggest
drop since Nov. 10.  Power Mate Technology Co. (8109)  (8109 TT), a maker of direct
current converters, dropped 5.6 percent to NT$33.80, the lowest
close since July 1, 2010. Sales in May sank 3.9 percent to
NT$65.93 million ($2.2 million) from a year earlier, according
to a Taiwan Stock Exchange statement.  Rexchip Electronics Co. (4932)  (4932 TT), a chipmaker, declined
3.2 percent to NT$8.62, the lowest close since March 28. May
sales slumped 19 percent to NT$2.68 billion from a year earlier,
according to a statement to the exchange.  Via Technologies Inc. (2388)  (2388 TT), a chipmaker, retreated 5.7
percent to NT$15.65, the biggest loss since March 29. Sales last
month dropped 16.3 percent to NT$300 million from a year
earlier, according to a statement filed to the  Taiwan Stock
Exchange .  To contact the reporter on this story:
